.TH "tracing_map_add_key_field" 9 "tracing_map_add_key_field" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tracing_map_add_key_field \- Add a field describing a tracing_map key
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tracing_map_add_key_field
.BI "(struct tracing_map *map "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "tracing_map_cmp_fn_t cmp_fn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map" 12
The tracing_map
.IP "offset" 12
The offset within the key
.IP "cmp_fn" 12
The comparison function that will be used to sort on the key
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Let the map know there is a key and that if it's used as a sort key
to use cmp_fn.

A key can be a subset of a compound key; for that purpose, the
offset param is used to describe where within the compound key
the key referenced by this key field resides.
.SH "RETURN"
The index identifying the field in the map and associated
tracing_map_elts, or -EINVAL on error.
